Package: CERMBweatheradmin
Title: Functions to manage a PostgreSQL database of weather station records
Version: 0.4.0
Date: 2021-07-26
Authors@R: c(
  person("Hamish", "Clarke", email = "hamishc@uow.edu.au", role = c("aut")),
  person("Michael", "Bedward", email = "michael.bedward@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")) )
Description: Tools developed by the Centre for Environmental Risk Management
  of Bushfires, University of Wollongong (Australia) to manage a PostgreSQL
  database of weather station data provided by the Australian Bureau of 
  Meteorology, and to calculate fire-related indices such as Forest Fire
  Danger Index..
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
